			<ns0:name>halya...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/112856509894568708731/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">&lt;b&gt;- Where are we today?&lt;/b&gt;
Any hardware exception terminates NaCl program immediately.

&lt;b&gt;- Why is this a problem?&lt;/b&gt;
The program can't exit gracefully in case of internal problems. The hardware exceptions can be used for null pointer checking in VMs. Null pointer exception handling can be usefull for managed programs.

&lt;b&gt;- The proposed enhancement:&lt;/b&gt;
Implement hardware exception handling via debugging on windows and other ways for linux and mac. The interface should allow to set handler function and alternative stack.

&lt;b&gt;- Exit criteria:&lt;/b&gt;
All 3 platforms support hardware exception handling in browser.

&lt;b&gt;- Anticipated impact:&lt;/b&gt;
On windows, all NaCl debuggers must implement exception handling code and so this code should be small.
